message.en_US: Well, well!\. A classic instant-matter wall!
[nods]
Let's go find this device.
It looks like this thing still works!
Hi?
Don't worry Lea.\. That isn't you.
These avatars are not actual players.
This machine will use one of these avatar templates to disguise your player account.
While you won't physically change appearance, the CrossWorlds servers will think that you are someone else.
This should make it impossible for our \c[1]blue friend\c[0] to track you again.
Regarding the one that looks exactly like you, it looks like the machine simply scanned your data when you walked in.
Go ahead and pick an avatar.
Lea?\. Let's use the machine.\. We didn't come all this way for nothing.
Don't worry, I know this thing is safe.\. The hacker who built this used it successfully for years.
[nods]
You want the same exact avatar you already have?
[nods]
Growing fond of the horns?
Don't worry about it.\. I'm only joking with you.
I believe it will still work just fine, as long as our \c[1]blue friend\c[0] never actually sees you.
And the chances of that happening in the official playground without his ability to track you are next to zero.
Oh,\. a \c[2]Triblader\c[0] avatar?
[nods]
That is a popular class, this will stand out even less than your \c[2]Spheromancer\c[0] would.
Oh,\. a \c[2]Triblader\c[0] avatar?
[nods]
This looks like one of the starter CrossWorlds avatar presets, I have seen this player avatar all over the place.
It should be the perfect disguise.
I think you need to step over there and the rest should be automatic.
Despite me being involved when the original hacker was caught, I never got to see how this actually worked.
Lea?\. Are you there?
[nods]
Wow, I think it's working!
You're showing up as a different player right now.
You still physically look the same, obviously,\. but the CrossWorlds server is showing you to be someone else.
Anyone on the outside trying to track us will never be able to do that, since they won't know who to look for!
Hi!
Indeed, let's return to the playground now.\. Remember that other girl that wanted to meet you?
[nods]
Hi!
Lea?\. Are you there?
[nods]
Wow, I think it's working!
You're showing up as a different player right now.
Other players and NPCs will still see you as your original \c[1]Spheronamcer\c[0] avatar.
But as far as the server is concerned, I am talking to an entirely different player.
Anyone on the outside trying to track us will never be able to do that, since they won't know who to look for!
Hi!
Indeed, let's return to the playground now.\. Remember that other girl that wanted to meet up with you?
[nods]
Head out through this teleporter when you're ready.\. I believe the machine is still active if you want to use it again.
Only a small number of staff were involved with catching the original hacker who built this.
Nobody should ever suspect that anyone would be using this equipment.
